ent%20data%20from%20the%20National%20Children's%20Health%20Survey%2C%20which%20covered%20the%202022%20and%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftop-private-equity-firms-investing-in-sports-teams-leagues-media-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Einvestors%3C%2Fa%3E%20ranging%20from%20venture%20capitalists%20to%20private%20equity%20have%20increasingly%20been%20paying%20attention%20to%20the%20deep%20connection%20Americans%20have%20with%20youth%20sports.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20look%20at%20wallet%20share%20and%20the%20statistics%20around%20that%20for%20parents%2C%20how%20much%20they%20will%20spend%20on%20youth%20sports%2C%20it's%20insane%2C%26quot%3B%20Aaron%20Miller%2C%20an%20investor%20at%20early-stage%20VC%20firm%20Will%20Ventures%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BFor%20the%20first%20time%2C%20institutional%20investors%20are%20realizing%20that%20these%20are%20really%20interesting%20assets%20to%20own%20and%20maybe%20even%20optimize.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMiller%20said%20the%20addressable%20market%20for%20youth%20sports%20is%20massive.%20According%20to%20The%20Aspen%20Institute's%20Project%20Play%2C%20the%20average%20US%20sports%20family%20spent%20%241%2C016%20on%20their%20child's%20primary%20sport%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMiller%20said%20the%20US%20is%20really%20the%20only%20country%20in%20the%20world%20with%20this%20level%20of%20spending%20on%20youth%20sports%2C%20which%20makes%20it%20attractive%20for%20investments.%20He%20said%20investments%20had%20grown%20in%20two%20areas%3A%20experiences%20and%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20new%20technologies%20in%20the%20space%20are%20using%20AI%2C%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgamechanger-artificial-intelligence-platform-track-analyze-youth-sports-games-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGameChanger%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20livestreaming%20and%20game%20management%20software%20that%20youth%20teams%20use%20to%20keep%20track%20of%20stats%20and%20film%2C%20and%20put%20together%20highlights.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnrivaled%20Sports%20is%20an%20example%20of%20a%20company%20pouring%20money%20into%20experiences.%20Josh%20Harris%2C%20the%20owner%20of%20the%20Washington%20Commanders%20and%20cofounder%20of%20Apollo%20Global%20Management%2C%20along%20with%20Blackstone's%20David%20Blitzer%2C%20co-invested%20their%20own%20money%20to%20launch%20the%20company%20this%20year.%20Unrivaled%20Sports%20specializes%20in%20creating%20unique%20experiences%20for%20kids%20who%20play%20baseball%2C%20soccer%2C%20football%2C%20and%20action%20sports%20and%20also%20recently%20got%20a%20further%20%24120%20million%20investment%2C%20led%20by%20Dick's%20Sporting%20Goods.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMiller's%20firm%20itself%20has%20invested%20in%20several%20youth%20sports%20companies%2C%20such%20as%20Youth%20Inc.%2C%20a%20media%20and%20commerce%20company%20founded%20by%20former%20NFLer%20Greg%20Olsen%2C%20and%20Aktivate%2C%20a%20sports%20tech%20platform%20for%20K-12%20schools.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20notable%20deals%20in%20the%20space%20include%20KKR%20acquiring%20Varsity%20Brands%20last%20year%2C%20and%20PlayOn%20(backed%20by%20KKR)%20buying%20MaxPreps%20from%20CBS%20Sports.%20TeamSnap%20acquired%20Mojo%2C%20a%20youth%20sports%20streaming%20service%2C%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInvesting%20in%20youth%20sports%20can%20also%20benefit%20leagues.%20Initiatives%20like%20the%20Junior%20NBA%20or%20LOVB's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-pe-firm-atwater-capital-is-investing-womens-sports-lovb-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eyouth%20programs%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20helping%20to%20grow%20the%20game%20at%20a%20young%20level.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20win%20over%20a%20kid%20in%20middle%20school%2C%20they're%20very%20influenceable%2C%20they%20could%20be%20loyal%20customers%20for%20the%20next%2050-plus%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20Miller%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2257919334-30a9-4f31-8815-357618ca1015%5C%22%3EDoes%20the%20money%20stop%20kids%20from%20being%20kids%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EConcerns%20about%20the%20professionalization%20of%20youth%20sports%20have%20been%20growing%20in%20the%20last%20few%20years%2C%20with%20some%20parents%20concerned%20about%20burnout%20or%20overuse%20injuries%20happening%20at%20younger%20ages.%20As%20part%20of%20its%20Project%20Play%20research%2C%20the%20Aspen%20Institute%20found%20that%20some%20parents%20felt%20pressure%20to%20have%20their%20children%20specialize%20in%20a%20sport%20at%20an%20earlier%20age.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20costs%20have%20also%20increased.%20The%20Aspen%20Institute%20reported%20a%2046%25%20increase%20in%20cost%20for%20a%20child's%20primary%20sport%20from%202019%20to%202024.%20The%20study%20found%20that%20spending%20on%20travel%20and%20lodging%2C%20team%20registration%20fees%2C%20and%20camps%20or%20private%20training%20contributed%20to%20the%20increase.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMelissa%20Jacobs%20is%20a%20journalist%20and%20the%20creator%20of%20the%20Good%20Game%20Substack%2C%20which%20focuses%20on%20talking%20about%20youth%20sports%20for%20parents.%20She%20said%20that%20destination%20youth%20sports%20tournaments%20and%20experiences%20have%20been%20proliferating.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20parents'%20inboxes%20can%20be%20%26quot%3Bflooded%20with%20emails%20saying%20come%20to%20Huntington%20Beach%2C%20come%20to%20Omaha%2C%20come%20to%20Florida%20for%20every%20single%20sport.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20making%20the%20equity%20gap%20humongous%2C%20and%20it's%20also%20watering%20down%20the%20experience%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMiller%20said%20he%20felt%20there%20needed%20to%20be%20a%20system%20to%20ensure%20that%20youth%20sports%20don't%20get%20over-optimized%20as%20more%20money%20flows%20into%20the%20space.%20Companies%20can%20offer%20services%20that%20can%20be%20great%20for%20talent%20development%20and%20earn%20more%20money.%20But%20this%20profess