%20an%20investment%20management%20firm.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20often%20that%20the%20bar%20is%20higher.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20issue%20at%20the%20moment%20is%20that%20while%20it%20may%20be%20appealing%20to%20adopt%20a%20wait-and-see%20approach%2C%20later%20is%20not%20synonymous%20with%20better.%20That's%20the%20calculation%20many%20Americans%20are%20facing%20now%3A%20Do%20I%20hold%20out%20on%20making%20a%20move%20now%20while%20things%20settle%20down%2C%20or%20do%20I%20take%20the%20risk%20that%20things%20will%20take%20a%20turn%20for%20the%20worse%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20we%20can%20do%20now%20is%20kind%20of%20read%20tea%20leaves%20on%20the%20future%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Chris%20Woods%2C%20a%20financial%20advisor%20who%20founded%20Silvis%20Financial.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20that%20old%20Wayne%20Gretzky%20quote%20about%20skating%20%26quot%3Bto%20where%20the%20puck%20is%20going%20to%20be%2C%20not%20where%20it%20has%20been.%26quot%3B%20The%20issue%20is%20that%20it's%20hard%20to%20guess%20where%20things%20are%20headed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you're%20building%20up%20to%20a%20major%20financial%20leap%2C%20you%20typically%20sit%20on%20it%20until%20some%20level%20of%20certainty%20hits.%20That's%20especially%20true%20in%20scenarios%20where%20there%20are%20serious%20penalties%20for%20changing%20your%20mind.%20I%20mean%2C%20sure%2C%20you%20can%20offload%20that%20new%20car%20six%20months%20later%2C%20but%20you'd%20probably%20rather%20not.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJonathan%20Parker%2C%20a%20finance%20professor%20at%20MIT%2C%20tells%20me%20that%20a%20big%20spike%20in%20uncertainty%20will%20cause%20people%20to%20delay%20major%20spending%20such%20as%20upgrading%20to%20a%20new%20car%2C%20noting%20that%20%26quot%3Byou%20might%20want%20that%20money%20for%20other%20purposes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20people%20make%20a%20big%20financial%20decision%2C%20such%20as%20buying%20a%20house%2C%20investing%2C%20or%20retiring%2C%20they%20want%20some%20level%20of%20buffer.%20They%20leave%20space%20for%20the%20possibility%20that%20some%20unexpected%20need%20will%20pop%20up%20%E2%80%94%20a%20medical%20emergency%2C%20an%20unexpected%20broken-down%20car%20or%20leaky%20roof%2C%20a%20lost%20job%2C%20a%20death%20in%20the%20family.%20Ideally%2C%20consumers%20don't%20want%20to%20just%20barely%20make%20their%20mortgage%2C%20wind%20up%20suddenly%20tapping%20the%20money%20they%20stowed%20away%20in%20their%20stock%20portfolio%2C%20or%20skimp%20on%20their%20day-to-day%20needs%20in%20retirement.%20When%20they%20take%20leaps%2C%20they%20want%20to%20leave%20a%20little%20side%20pot%20available%20to%20avoid%20an%20unforeseen%20circumstance.%20There's%20only%20so%20much%20a%20person%20can%20control%20%E2%80%94%20doing%20the%20best%20job%20possible%20at%20work%20doesn't%20insulate%20you%20from%20layoffs%20or%20guarantee%20your%20pay%20will%20increase%20with%20prices.%20Uncertainty%20makes%20that%20buffer%20harder%20to%20calculate%20and%20feel%20confident%20about%20having%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20a%20time%20of%20great%20uncertainty%2C%20it's%20probably%20not%20the%20time%20you%20want%20to%20stretch%20with%20a%20purchase%2C%26quot%3B%20Sahm%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20uncertainty%20may%20be%20headache-inducing%20for%20individuals%20trying%20to%20make%20up%20their%20minds%2C%20but%20what%20it%20might%20mean%20for%20the%20broader%20economy%20is%20tricky.%20Consumer%20spending%20is%20America's%20economic%20engine%20%E2%80%94%20personal%20expenditures%20account%20for%20about%20two-thirds%20of%20GDP.%20Ironically%2C%20people%20being%20worried%20is%2C%20in%20part%2C%20supporting%20the%20economy.%20When%20consumers%20are%20concerned%20about%20prices%20going%20up%2C%20they%20may%20pull%20forward%20big%20purchases%20to%20get%20them%20out%20of%20the%20way%20now%20before%20they%20get%20more%20expensive%20later.%20If%20you're%20nervous%20about%20your%20washing%20machine%20or%20car%20going%20kaput%20soon%20or%20are%20just%20looking%20to%20upgrade%2C%20it%20may%20feel%20prudent%20to%20replace%20them%20sooner%20rather%20than%20later%20in%20case%20prices%20go%20up.%20This%20year%2C%20consumer%20spending%20has%20jumped%20because%20of%20people%20trying%20to%20get%20ahead%20of%20tariffs.%20Crummy%20feelings%20about%20the%20future%20of%20the%20economy%20have%20actually%20been%20a%20good%20thing%2C%20spending-wise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20one%20thing%20that%20has%20helped%20consumer%20spending%20stay%20up%20while%20sentiment%20has%20really%20cratered%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Scott%20Baker%2C%20an%20associate%20finance%20professor%20at%20Northwestern%20University's%20Kellogg%20School%20of%20Management.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20once%20people%20have%20made%20these%20anticipatory%20purchases%20or%20start%20to%20batten%20down%20the%20hatches%2C%20they%20could%20bring%20down%20the%20economy%20with%20them.%20If%20someone%20decides%20to%20put%20off%20renovating%20their%20kitchen%2C%20it%20means%20the%20contractor%2C%20the%20workers%2C%20and%20the%20store%20selling%20the%20materials%20miss%20out%20on%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BJust%20the%20fact%20that%20all%20of%20this%20is%20happening%20generates%20a%20wave%20of%20uncertainty%2C%26quot%3B%20Parker%20says.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20significant%20drag%20on%20the%20economy%2C%20and%20it's%20not%20clear%20how%20big%2C%20but%20it%20certainly%20is%20a%20drag.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20sure%2C%20there%20are%20some%20areas%20where%20sitting%20on%20your%20hands%20is%20usually%20the%20way%20to%20go%2C%20such%20as%20investing.%20When%20the%20going%20gets%20tough%20in%20the%20stock%20market%2C%20one%20of%20the%20worst%20things%20people%20can%20do%20is%20panic%20and%20cash%20out%20at%20the%20bottom.%20If%20someone%20had%20done%20that%2C%20say%2C%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20Trump's%20%26quot%3BLiberation%20Day%2C%26quot%3B%20they'd%20probably%20regret%20it%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMarkets%20fluctuate%20all%20the%20time%2C%20they%20will%20go%20up%20and%20down%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Siavash%20Radpour%2C%20the%20associate%20director%20of%20the%20Retirement%20Equity%20Lab%20at%20The%20New%20School's%20Schwartz%20Center%20for%20Economic%20Policy%20Analysis.%20%26quot%3BNot%20doing%20anything%20is%20often%20a%20good%20policy%20for%20people%20who%20don't%20know%20what's%20going%20on.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20colleagues%20at%20Business%20Insider%20recently%20did%20a%20series%20of%20stories%20attempting%20to%20answer%20whether%20it's%20a%20good%20time%20to%20make%20big%20life%20decisions.%20They%20looked%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fshould-you-start-a-business-during-recession-general-economic-uncertainty-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Estarting%20a%20business%20%3C%2Fa%3E(the%20answer%20was%20yes)%2C%20buying%20a%20home%20(if%20you%20must%2C%20but%20maybe%20rent)%2C%20changing%20jobs%20(no)%2C%20investing%20in%20stocks%20(go%20for%20it%2C%20within%20reason)%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbuying-car-vehicle-new-used-good-time-economic-uncertainty-tariffs-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebuying%20a%20new%20car%3C%2Fa%3E%20(hop%20to%20it)%2C%20and%20retiring%20(hold%20off).%20The%20advice%20in%20the%20stories%20is%20all%20helpful%20and%20enlightening%2C%20but%20it%20can%20also%20go%20only%20so%20far.%20Every%20decision%20in%20life%20involves%20risks%2C%20and%20the%20truest%20answer%20to%20%26quot%3BShould%20I%20do%20X%2C%20Y%2C%20Z%3F%26quot%3B%20is%2C%20%26quot%3BIt%20depends!%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20no%20denying%20we're%20in%20a%20time%20of%20heightened%20uncertainty.%20Anyone%20who%20says%20they%20know%20what%20will%20happen%20next%20is%20lying.%20And%20it%20really%20feels%20like%20things%20could%20break%20in%20any%20direction.%20While%20the%20safest%20advice%20is%20probably%20that%20you%20should%20snap%20up%20that%20new%20car%20before%20tariffs%20push%20up%20prices%20by%20thousands%20of%20dollars%2C%20Trump%20could%20declare%20the%20tariff%20thing%20over%20tomorrow%2C%20and%20all%20of%20a%20sudden%20you've%20overpaid%20for%20no%20reason.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20market%20this%20year%20has%20been%20driven%20less%20by%20fundamentals%20and%20just%20more%20by%20the%20different%20news%20we're%20getting%20from%20week%20to%20week%20on%20what's%20going%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20Woods%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaybe%20you%20do%20hold%20off%20on%20buying%20a%20house%20and%20come%20to%20regret%20it%20five%20years%20from%20now%20when%20prices%20are%20even%20higher.%20Or%2C%20you%20don't%20retire%2C%20and%20you%20miss%20out%20on%20time%20with%20your%20grandkids%2C%20or%20you're%20so%20risk-averse%20about%20jumping%20ship%20from%20your%20company%20that%20you%20miss%20out%20on%20your%20dream%20job.%20Those%20decisions%20are%20harder%20to%20make%20now%20with%20more%20factors%20in%20play.%20It's%20not%20just%20whether%20a%20recession%20is%20coming%2C%20but%20also%20what%20the%20AI%20revolution%20means%20for%20the%20structural%20future%20of%20the%20labor%20market.%20The%20question%20for%20retirees%20isn't%20just%20whether%20they've%20saved%20enough%3B%20it's%20also%20what%20might%20happen%20with%20public%20assistance%20programs%20they'd%20long%20planned%20around.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20the%20risk%20of%20what's%20going%20to%20happen%20to%20Medicaid%2C%20what's%20going%20to%20happen%20to%20Social%20Security%2C%26quot%3B%20Radpour%20says.%20%26quot%3BHealth%20expenses%20are%20really%20scary%20in%20retirement.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStarting%20a%20new%20business%20is%20always%20risky%20%E2%80%94%20statistically%20speaking%2C%20half%20of%20new%20businesses%20fail%20in%20five%20years.%20Loans%20for%20starting%20said%20business%20are%20more%20expensive%20and%20harder%20to%20come%20by.%20While%20it%20may%20be%20a%20decent%20time%20for%20a%20startup%2C%20no%20plan%20is%20foolproof.%20Many%20people%20who%20start%20a%20company%20during%20downturns%20and%20turmoil%20are%20doing%20so%20because%20they've%20lost%20their%20job%20or%20someone%20in%20their%20household%20has%2C%20not%20because%20they're%20jazzed%20about%20the%20future.%20%26quot%3BThe%20jump%20is%20made%20for%20them%2C%20in%20some%20sense%2C%26quot%3B%20Baker%20says.%20Still%2C%20if%20you%20see%20a%20market%20opportunity%20and%20want%20to%20make%20the%20jump%2C%20the%20idea%20that%20economy%20could%20get%20bad%20shouldn't%20preclude%20taking%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThinking%20through%20all%20of%20the%20ambiguity%20and%20confusion%20isn't%20fun.%20Financial%20risks%20are%20always%20scary%2C%20whether%20big%20or%20small.%20Now%20it%20feels%20like%20the%20anxiety%20is%20extra%20heightened%2C%20given%20the%20context.%20For%20many%20people%2C%20it's%20going%20to%20feel%20like%20they're%20damned%20if%20they%20do%2C%20damned%20if%20they%20don't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20are%20going%20to%20get%20burned%20on%20either%20side%20of%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20Sahm%20says.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20for%20what%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Femily-stewart%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEmily%20Stewart%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%2C%20writing%20about%20business%20and%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbig-purchases-financial-risks-economic-uncertainty-real-estate-careers-2025-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1749976621000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6841fffdc19ab3675c10c365%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbig-purchases-financial-risks-economic-uncertainty-real-estate-careers-2025-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Americans%20are%20uneasy%20about%20buying%20real%20estate%2C%20changing%20careers%2C%20and%20more.%20Here's%20